      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-02-16T18:21:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don’t think that there’s any way to know this (like a task manager kill) in-process on Windows.\n\nIt’s kind of the same on POSIX, you’re killed without prejudice if someone sends you a SIGKILL, but we can catch the signals that might be tried before SIGKILL.",
      "revId": "eba544bca32950b47522bc6f339898a2dfc8755a",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "50d81603_e3711594",
        "filename": "util/misc/metrics.h",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 148,
      "author": {
        "id": 1144260
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-02-16T18:40:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes, TerminateProcess() is undetectable afaik, without adding a debugger wrapper or something.\n\nWe\u0027d get these as a console app/tests... https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/desktop/ms683242(v\u003dvs.85).aspx but I don\u0027t think in the field embedded in Chrome.\n\nEmbedded in Chrome we could get WM_CLOSE  https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/desktop/ms632617(v\u003dvs.85).aspx or WM_QUERYENDSESSION. I\u0027m not sure if it\u0027s worth making a message HWND for this purpose though. (base/win/message_window.h for reference if you feel it\u0027s useful.)",
      "parentUuid": "bccf9d14_b9580637",
      "revId": "eba544bca32950b47522bc6f339898a2dfc8755a",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "76c0efaa_721469b0",
        "filename": "util/misc/metrics.h",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 148,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-02-16T19:40:04Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e Yes, TerminateProcess() is undetectable afaik, without adding a debugger wrapper or something.\n\u003e \n\u003e We\u0027d get these as a console app/tests... https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/desktop/ms683242(v\u003dvs.85).aspx but I don\u0027t think in the field embedded in Chrome.\n\u003e \n\u003e Embedded in Chrome we could get WM_CLOSE  https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/desktop/ms632617(v\u003dvs.85).aspx or WM_QUERYENDSESSION. I\u0027m not sure if it\u0027s worth making a message HWND for this purpose though. (base/win/message_window.h for reference if you feel it\u0027s useful.)\n\nThanks for the pointers.\n\nI started heading down the WM_CLOSE road and then realized that it’d probably mean taking on a dependency on user32. I know that we don’t want that in the client. Is it OK in the handler?",
      "parentUuid": "50d81603_e3711594",
      "revId": "eba544bca32950b47522bc6f339898a2dfc8755a",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "c98d1bec_7ccc7590",
        "filename": "util/misc/metrics.h",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 148,
      "author": {
        "id": 1144260
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-02-16T19:49:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Good question ...\n\nBut it looks like we already have a dependency on advapi32.dll for ImpersonateNamedPipeClient() and RevertToSelf(), and advapi32 in turn has a user32 dependency. I\u0027m not sure if it tries to delayload that or not, but in practice when I look at chrome --type\u003dcrashpad-handler it has user32 loaded. So I don\u0027t think this would be regressing anything.",
      "parentUuid": "76c0efaa_721469b0",
      "revId": "eba544bca32950b47522bc6f339898a2dfc8755a",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    }
